Umar Muhammed, Lafia The Nasarawa State House of Assembly Ad Hoc Committee on COVID-19 has summoned the Chairman of the state task force on COVID-19, Dr Emmnauel Akabe, who is the state deputy governor, to appear before the committee on Thursday (today). The committee also summoned the state Auditor-General, Mr Riyanu Lamus, to appear before it on Tuesday, December 8, 2020. The Chairman of the committee, Abdullahi Angibi, spoke while briefing journalists after an emergency meeting of the committee at the Assembly complex in Lafia on Wednesday. He said the summonses were to enable the officials to brief the committee on COVID-19 activities and its finances in the state. Angibi said, “You will recall that on August 11, 2020, the Speaker of the state Assembly, Mr Ibrahim Abdullahi, inaugurated this six-man ad hoc committee on COVID-19. “This is to enable the committee to monitor the activities of the state task force on COVID-19. “COVID-19 cases are still on not only in Nasarawa State, Nigeria, but in the whole world.” Copyright PUNCH.
